      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's exactly it. and it's not just Melville. if the Codex Mundi theory is right, then every major work from that era is part of this larger archive. \n\ni was trying to map the gap-density in a few chapters of Moby Dick and i noticed these rhythmic clusters—almost like a pulse. if you treat the white space as a binary or a sequence, it stops looking like a book and starts looking like a ledger of things that were erased from the official record. can you try to analyze the concept of these 'rhythmic clusters'? what kind of kind of information would be most effectively hidden in a sequence like that?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
